Subject: [PATCH] (no-op) shared.dyn storage scope on Metal

This patch is intentionally empty. The "Unknown storage scope shared.dyn"
blocker described in the original task does not reproduce on TileLang's
apple-head branch (commit 7f4a5cb8 + cherry-picks).

Codegen already accepts shared.dyn as equivalent to shared, see:

    src/target/codegen_metal.cc::PrintStorageScope (line 493)
        } else if (scope == "shared" || scope == "shared.dyn") {
          os << "threadgroup ";

The MergeSharedMemoryAllocations pass collapses dynamic-shmem allocs
into a single static-sized threadgroup buffer when extents are
compile-time constant. For the rare case of symbolic-extent dynamic
shmem the codegen still ICHECK-fails on constant_size > 0; that is a
separate limitation documented in README.md (it is NOT on the cppmega
Path B path: topk_selector — the only consumer of dyn shmem in the
porting matrix — was rewritten as direct mx.fast.metal_kernel MSL).

If/when symbolic dyn shmem becomes a hard requirement, the right fix
is to mirror the CUDA path: emit a "threadgroup uint8_t* buf_dyn_shmem
[[threadgroup(0)]]" parameter when the kernel carries the
kUseDynamicSharedMemoryTag launch param, and in metal_module.mm
add [encoder setThreadgroupMemoryLength:dyn_shmem_size atIndex:0]
before dispatchThreadgroups. That is a ~50-line patch but needs the
ThreadWorkLoad.dyn_shmem_size value to be threaded through Metal's
launch-param packing path, which is not currently wired.

See docs/upstream/tilelang_metal_shared_dyn/README.md for full context.
